Pariveda was created on the foundation of talent development. We are challenged each day to continue learning as we work toward reaching our fullest potential. 

Russell Clarkson, a Vice President out of our Dallas office asks, "In a world moving at an incredible rate of speed, how is it possible to keep up with what is current, new or changing?" Russell has always been a "learning junkie" but the flood of information that we get from blogs, websites, podcasts, TED talks and mainstream print media can be a little overwhelming. And it still seems we are only getting part of the story.

Join us for #ThoughtLeadershipThursday and read about Russell's experience with Massive Open Online Course (MOOC) http://bit.ly/ContinuousLearning #TLT

Orlando is in our hearts and Pariveda cares deeply about those impacted, both physically and emotionally by this senseless act which caused the deaths and injuries to so many individuals this week. We express our deep sympathy to the victims, families, the people of Orlando, and the Lesbian, Gay, Bisexual, Transgender (LGBT) community now forever changed by the massacre at the Pulse nightclub. 
 
Pariveda supports acceptance, diversity and equality. We respect all people regardless of ethnicity, race, religion, or sexual orientation and support their freedom. We are especially reminded in times like these of the greatness of our nation built on supporting the individual's freedom of life, liberty and the pursuit of happiness. This freedom cannot be stripped away by hateful acts.  

Pariveda is sending nourishing snacks to the blood donation center just one mile from the Pulse nightclub where the shootings occurred. Many people are waiting in long lines to donate blood, and we hope to support the well-being of both donors and workers and to express our sympathy and support in this way to the Orlando community. #parivedacares
Yay!

San Francisco Fins recently volunteered to help serve meals to those in need! 

The Volunteer Resource Program at GLIDE places about 10,000 volunteers each year, totaling 65,000 hours of service.
 
Serving a meal in the Daily Free Meals Program is a transformative experience. This program requires 85 volunteers each day to fill the breakfast, prep, lunch and dinner shifts, 364 days a year. Our SF Fins were able to fill some of those volunteer shifts for the day! Volunteers assist with everything from serving food, to bussing tables, to handing out silverware and condiments. 

Well done!

Over the last month, the Dallas office collected over 40 board games to donate to The Family Place. Last Friday night, June 3rd, a group of Fins brought these games to The Family Place's campus that serves as a home for families that have been displaced by domestic violence. The donations were met by dozens of smiling faces that were excited to have a new game to play and new people to play them with. We had a very successful night where we played for over 3 hours, donated more than half of the games directly to the families, and suffered no injuries from fallen Jenga towers! The rest of the donations were given to the staff who will keep the games on site to be used and handed out to families as they see fit.

A huge thank you to every person who donated their time, energy, and games to this event and organization!

We can't wait for our third #ParivedaPerspectives event in New York on Wednesday! Tom Cunningham and Greg Leflar with The Sound of the Future: Predictive Analytics and the Transformation of the Music Industry
 
Join Greg Leflar, Vice President in Houston, and Thomas Cunningham, Vice President in New York, as they explore the transformation that predictive analytics has already wrought on the modern business environment and look into the future at what's next as more industries become dependent on sophisticated data analysis to support everything from strategic planning to day-to-day operations. The music business is a fascinating test case for what happens when technological innovation upends an entire industry – is predictive analytics coming to the rescue? Why are Pandora, Spotify, and Apple all buying predictive analytics companies? What is the future for the music industry in the face of rapidly changing consumption patterns? Enjoy an evening of stimulating thought-pieces and scintillating conversation and while sipping fine wines at the Film Society of Lincoln Center with Pariveda Solutions.

Our Seattle Fins we were able to clean and maintain a fleet of 75 bicycles, tricycles, and more with Outdoors for All Foundation! Thanks to all the help and experience from our team there will be enough bikes for future events and demonstrations and plenty available for individuals to rent upon request. 

The Outdoors for All Foundation transforms lives through outdoor recreation.  Founded in 1979 in the Pacific Northwest, Outdoors for All is a national leader in delivering adaptive and therapeutic recreation for children and adults with disabilities. Each year more than 2,400 individuals exercise their abilities thanks to the training and support of more than 700 volunteers. Outdoors for All enriches the lives of individuals with disabilities and families and helps them to get out and enjoy the great outdoors. Outdoors for All's programs includes snowboarding, snowshoeing, cross country and downhill skiing, cycling, hiking, river rafting, kayaking, day camps, rock-climbing, camping and custom events.

status_message: Over the holidays, the New York office participated in toy drives at Embrace the Kids and The Family Center. The organizations work with children who suffer from a serious illness or whose parents suffer from a serious illness. New York Fins helped organize gifts donated through the drive.

Throughout November and December, Chicago Fins collected food items and monetary donations for a 2nd Grade Class at the Curtis School of Excellence in Chicago's South Side. At school, the children are provided both breakfast and lunch at school and often don't eat a consistent dinner. During the holiday break, most students will not eat regular meals at home. With Pariveda's donations, each student was supplied with a bag of ready-to-eat food, toiletries, and winter gloves the last day before break.
